<emphasis box="[151,316,1371,1396]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Saica apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[331,474,1370,1396]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24. 22" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1402,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1394,1930]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. 22. Paratagalis spinosus, female, head and pronotum, dorsal view. Figs. 23 – 24, Saica apicalis, male, 23, dorsal view; 24, head and pronotum, lateral view, the arrow points the posterior pronotal spine." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182465/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
Figs. 
<number box="[397,474,1370,1396]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="23.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="23.0">23–24</number>
</figureCitation>
), originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[798,925,1370,1396]" name="Guatemala" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
(Osborn &amp; Drake 
<number box="[1143,1205,1370,1396]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1915.0">1915</number>
), has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[216,312,1410,1436]" name="Panama" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[325,503,1410,1436]" name="French Guiana" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[516,591,1410,1436]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[654,771,1410,1436]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McAtee" box="[787,1091,1410,1436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="53" refString="McAtee, W. L. and Malloch, J. R. (1923) Notes on American Bactrodinae and Saicinae (Heteroptera: Reduviidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 16, 247 - 255." type="journal article" year="1923">
McAtee &amp; Malloch 
<number box="[1029,1091,1410,1436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1923.0">1923</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Villiers" box="[1105,1262,1410,1436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="53" refString="Villiers, A. (1943) Catalogue des Saicitae (Hem. Reduviidae). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 15, 318 - 323." type="journal article" year="1943">
Villiers 
<number box="[1200,1262,1410,1436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wygodzinsky" pageId="7" pageNumber="53" refString="Wygodzinsky, P. (1949) Elenco sistematico de los reduviiformes americanos. Instituto de Medicina Regional de la Universidad Nacional de Tucuman, Monografia, 1, 1 - 102." type="journal article" year="1949">
Wygodzinsky 
<number box="[151,213,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1949.0">1949</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Froeschner" box="[228,431,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1988) Family Reduviidae Latreille, 1807. The Assassin Bugs. In: Henry, T. J. &amp; Froeschner, R. C. (Eds.), Catalog of the Heteroptera, or true bugs, of Canada and the continental United States. E. Brill, New York, pp. 616 - 651." type="book chapter" year="1988">
Froeschner 
<number box="[369,431,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado" box="[447,654,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="53" refString="Maldonado, C. J. (1990) Systematic catalogue of the Reduviidae of the World, Caribbean Journal of Science, Special publication No. 1, University of Puerto Rico, Mayaguez, Puerto Rico, 694 pp." type="book" year="1990">
Maldonado 
<number box="[592,654,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Melo &amp; Coscarón 
<number box="[898,960,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1994.0">1994</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana" box="[976,1338,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Marques, O. M. (2005) Primeiro registro de Saica apicalis Osborn &amp; Drake para o Brasil e Pseudosaica florida (Barber), com notas taxonomicas e chave para os generos de Saicinae do Brasil (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 22, 405 - 409." type="journal article" year="2005">
Gil-Santana &amp; Marques 
<number box="[1274,1338,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Elkins" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" refString="Elkins, J. C. (1951) The Reduviidae of Texas. Texas Journal of Science, 4, 408 - 412." type="journal article" year="1951">
Elkins (
<number box="[159,220,1490,1516]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1951.0">1951</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from Texas, 
<collectingCountry box="[637,699,1490,1516]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">USA</collectingCountry>
, based on a single specimen collected at light. However, Blinn (
<number box="[159,220,1530,1556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="1990.0">1990</number>
) considered the presence of 
<taxonomicName box="[567,692,1531,1556]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Saica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[567,692,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">S. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Texas could be a result of an accidental introduction of an exotic species, or a labeling error. This author also considered the species widely distributed in Central 
<collectingCountry name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">America</collectingCountry>
south of 
<collectingCountry box="[295,388,1610,1636]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, without further consideration of specimens examined or countries included.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1370,1796]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana" box="[197,565,1650,1676]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Marques, O. M. (2005) Primeiro registro de Saica apicalis Osborn &amp; Drake para o Brasil e Pseudosaica florida (Barber), com notas taxonomicas e chave para os generos de Saicinae do Brasil (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 22, 405 - 409." type="journal article" year="2005">
Gil-Santana &amp; Marques (
<number box="[495,557,1650,1676]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
related the variability of the posterior pronotal spines in 
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1364,1651,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Saica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[1241,1364,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">S. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from long to imperceptible. The specimen studied here has moderately long posterior pronotal spines (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1375,1690,1716]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24. 22" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1402,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1394,1930]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. 22. Paratagalis spinosus, female, head and pronotum, dorsal view. Figs. 23 – 24, Saica apicalis, male, 23, dorsal view; 24, head and pronotum, lateral view, the arrow points the posterior pronotal spine." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182465/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[1342,1375,1690,1716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
